co.cask.cdap.api.messaging

Interface MessagePublisher


  • @Beta
public interface MessagePublisher
    Provides access to publish messages to the transactional messaging system. Note that for instances acquired through the MessagingContext.getMessagePublisher() method and when any of the publish methods is called within a transactional context, exceptions may not be thrown right away to indicate the error, but rather at the transaction commit time. If Transactional.execute(TxRunnable) was used to execute the transaction, exception will always be wrapped inside a TransactionFailureException.

      • publish

        void publish(String namespace,
           String topic,
           Charset charset,
           String... payloads)
             throws TopicNotFoundException,
                    IOException
        Publishes messages to the given topic. Each payload string will be encoded as byte array using the given charset.
        Parameters:
        namespace - namespace of the topic
        topic - name of the topic
        charset - the Charset for encoding the payload Strings.
        payloads - the payloads to publish. Each element in the array will become a Message.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the topic name is invalid. A valid id should only contain alphanumeric characters and _ or -.
        IOException - if failed to communicate with the messaging system.
        TopicNotFoundException - if the give topic doesn't exist
